definitions.definition: The study and interpretation of behavior in terms of simple and complex reflexes.

A form of complementary medicine involving the stimulation of points on the feet, hands, or ears, in the belief that it will have a beneficial effect on some other parts of the body or to improve general health.

main_definition: ( medicine ) The study and interpretation of behavior in terms of simple and complex reflexes.
secondary_definitions: ( alternative medicine ) A form of complementary medicine involving the stimulation of points on the feet, hands, or ears, in the belief that it will have a beneficial effect on some other parts of the body or to improve general health.
